Subject: Re: [T2] Battery Size (CCA)??

On 12/22/03 7:29 PM, "Dave" <brooksdj(-at-)earthlink.net> wrote:

> What's everyone using as for battery rating (cranking amps) in there Buses?  I
> bought one for the 67 Panel that was 450 CCA but seems weak.  I noticed
> Wal-Mart sale a Max something with 1000 CCA. Anyone had luck with this?

Are you sure that's not 1000 CA (-at-)32F? Otherwise that's an awful lot of
energy for a battery that can still fit in your engine compartment.

The smaller size 42 battery will be around 450 CCA. The larger, standard for
a bus, size 41 battery will have a much higher rating: 40-50% more typical.

